This is no longer an API break.  I've reverted the tests I updated (and/or forked them into specific tests for the new functionality).

The new API adds an explicit boolean parameter to tell the bottom sheet whether it should expect to be controlled by a `BottomSheetScrollController` (in which case there needs to be a `ScrollView` child with `primary: true`), or using the legacy method with a GestureDetector/AnimationController.

@HansMuller @goderbauer this is ready for review again.

But this is then inconsistent with added documentation:
  /// the sheet should take at the start.  The `clampTop` parameter specifies
  /// whether to force the bottom sheet to always be at least that height, and
  /// setting it to true will disable swipe down dismissal of the bottom sheet.

@eseidel 

> I don't think we should consider synchronous methods like native extensions at this time

why is that?
